Class 4

CSS Selectors (Cascading Styling Sheet)

It is another way of locating elements uniquely
Syntax:
tagname[attribute = 'attribute value']

example: input[id = 'user-message']

Css does not give you an opportunity to identify and element by text

Shortcuts for CSS:
Shortcut fro className: "." -- classname
    tagname.classNameValue
    input.form-control

Shortcut for ID: "#" -- ID
    tagname#idValue
    input#ctl00_MainContent_username

contains() method in css:
* symbol represents contains() method = tagname[attribute *= 'partial attribute value']
input[id *= 'user']

starts-with method in css:
^ symbol represents starts-with method -- tagname[attribute ^= 'starting attribute value']
input[type ^= 'sub']

ends-with method in css:
$ symbol represents ends-with method -- tagname[attribute $= 'ending attribute value']
input[id $= 'word']


WebElement Commands:
consist of several methods where we can perform actions and get element state
on the web page

isEnabled() -- boolean value
isSelected() -- boolean value
isDisplayed() -- boolean value
clear() -- void
getText() -- String value
getAttribute() -- String value

